LXII. The father of Terentius Priscus (Preiace to this book) prepares to celebrate his son’s return to his native land (Spain) by keeping the Saturnalia with more festivity than usual, combining, in fact, the Saturnalian feast with festivities in honour of his son's return. Martial invites the god to grace the feast with his presence.
